1) Steps to Install Docker on Windows

The following steps are involved in installing Docker Desktop on Windows:

Step 1: Check System Requirements
Windows 10/11 64-bit
Minimum 4 GB RAM
Virtualization enabled
WSL 2 backend supported

Docker Desktop on Windows officially supports WSL 2 (recommended).

Step 2: Enable WSL 2

Open PowerShell as Administrator:

wsl --install

Restart the system after installation.

Step 3: Download Docker Desktop

Download Docker Desktop from official Docker website:

Download Docker Desktop for Windows

The official Windows installation flow is provided by Docker Desktop docs.

Step 4: Install Docker Desktop
Double-click Docker Desktop Installer.exe
Select:
✅ Use WSL 2 instead of Hyper-V
✅ Add desktop shortcut
Click OK → Install
Restart system

Docker’s official installer recommends the WSL 2 engine on Windows.

Step 5: Launch Docker
Open Docker Desktop
Wait until whale icon becomes active
Verify installation:
docker --version
Step 6: Test Docker

Run first container:

docker run hello-world

This verifies that Docker Engine, CLI, and Desktop are working correctly.

2) Common Docker Commands

Below are the important Docker commands usually asked in lab exams.

a) Check Docker Version
docker --version
b) Download an Image
docker pull ubuntu

Downloads image from Docker Hub.

c) List Images
docker images
d) Run a Container
docker run -it ubuntu
e) Run Container in Background
docker run -d nginx
f) List Running Containers
docker ps
g) List All Containers
docker ps -a
h) Stop Container
docker stop <container_id>
i) Start Container
docker start <container_id>
j) Remove Container
docker rm <container_id>
k) Remove Image
docker rmi ubuntu
l) Build Docker Image
docker build -t myapp .

Builds image from Dockerfile.

m) Execute Command Inside Container
docker exec -it <container_id> bash
n) View Logs
docker logs <container_id>
